TITLE: Retrieving Event Logs with Web3.js in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: A TypeScript example showing how to retrieve past event logs from the Ethereum blockchain using Web3.js. This code demonstrates setting up filtering options to specifically look for Transfer events from a particular contract address within a specified block range.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web3/web3.js/blob/4.x/docs/docs/glossary/index.md#2025-04-21_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { Web3 } from 'web3';
const web3 = new Web3('https://mainnet.infura.io/v3/YOUR_INFURA_PROJECT_ID');

const options = {
  fromBlock: 0,
  toBlock: 'latest',
  address: '0xYourContractAddress',
  topics: [
    web3.utils.sha3('Transfer(address,address,uint256)')
  ]
};

web3.eth.getPastLogs(options)
  .then((logs) => {
    console.log(logs);
  })
  .catch((error) => {
    console.error('Error retrieving logs:', error);
  });
`
```

